  <refnamediv>
    <refname>rce_train</refname>

    <refpurpose>create a reduced coulomb energy or RCE network</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Calling Sequence</title>

    <synopsis>net = rce_train(train_samples, train_labels, lambdam, epsilon)</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsection>
    <title>Parameters</title>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>train_samples</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>dim*num data matrix; each column is a data point</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>train_labels</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>1*num vector of labels of each training sample</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>lambdam</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>maximal radius</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>epsilon</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>parameter used in D(x,x')-epsilon with defaul value
          1e-4</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>net</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>a reduced coulomb energy network</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsection>

  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>

    <para>Reduced coulomb energy of RCE network is one representative method
    of <emphasis>potential functions</emphasis>, which is the simplest method
    of some relaxation techniques. This function is to create a RCE
    network.</para>
  </refsection>

